AWS Databases:

	AWS provides customers with pay as you go pricing on a variety of cloud database services.

	These services can be accessed through a variety of means, including the AWS Command Line Interface, SDKs, and the AWS Management Console.

	Of these options, the AWS Management Console is arguably the most straight-forward and easy to use.

	For our purposes, it appears that the Amazon EC2 service may be most optimal.

	Amazon EC2 - 

		The Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) service is notable for its resizability.
		
		It allows users to choose how much space and compute power they need for their database.

		This makes for a compute cloud that is both powerful and cost-effective.